current research projects

one major project is the
 sather
language, compiler, libraries and system. my personal work is focusing
on the parallel extension which we call psather.

 the other major current project is the
l0  effort in natural
language learning.
 




students

 david
bailey is working on a computational model of the acquisition and
interpretation of verb phrases describing simple hand actions.

 chris bregler
is a grad. student in computer science interested in
computer vision, speech recognition, and the relation of both.

 ben gomes

 srinivas narayanan

 jonathan segal

 david stoutamire
maintains the 
sather
and psather language spec and compiler.  his thesis topic is exploiting
garbage collection to implement dynamic object-based locality
maintenance.

 boris vaysman





